---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Giscus from '../components/Giscus.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const VERSION = '3.5.5';
const baseUrl = `https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/releases/download/v${VERSION}`;
---

<Layout
  title="What's new in SoloMD v3.5.5"
  description="A 6-week-old Windows UI font regression finally diagnosed and fixed. Telemetry migrated off Aptabase to a self-hosted Cloudflare D1 endpoint. Plus PR #48 from @beihai23 with PDF export timeout, outline-in-tab, mermaid overlay contrast."
  lang={lang}
>
  <Header lang={lang} />
  <main>
    <article class="container whats-new">
      <nav class="breadcrumbs">
        <a href="/">Home</a> / <span>What's new</span>
      </nav>

      <p class="version-row">
        <span class="version-tag">v{VERSION}</span>
        <time>April 2026</time>
      </p>
      <h1>Win font fix, self-hosted analytics, polish.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Three things rolled into one patch: a <strong>6-week-old Windows
        UI font regression</strong> finally diagnosed and fixed, telemetry
        migrated <strong>off Aptabase to our own Cloudflare D1
        endpoint</strong> (zero third-party SaaS in the data path), and
        a <strong>polish PR from @beihai23</strong> covering PDF export
        timeout, outline button location, and Mermaid overlay contrast.
      </p>

      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href={`${baseUrl}/SoloMD_${VERSION}_universal.dmg`}>⬇ Download v{VERSION} (Mac)</a>
        <a class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" href={`${baseUrl}/SoloMD_${VERSION}_x64_en-US.msi`}>Download (Windows)</a>
        <a class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" href={`https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/releases/tag/v${VERSION}`}>All assets →</a>
      </div>

      <section>
        <h2>🇨🇳 The Windows UI font fix (issue #43)</h2>
        <p>
          From v0.1.12 onward, Win11 users saw the UI Chinese render
          slightly thin and inconsistent — visibly different from native
          ClearType. The cause: a bundled <code>"SoloMD CJK"</code>
          font (a 43&nbsp;KB LXGW WenKai subset, intended as the
          iOS-Simulator fallback) was placed <em>first</em> in the
          font-family chain. Combined with its
          <code>unicode-range: U+3400-9FFF</code>, this told every
          browser: <em>"for any CJK character, prefer SoloMD CJK over
          everything that follows"</em>. So Windows YaHei, macOS PingFang,
          Linux Noto Sans CJK — all bypassed.
        </p>
        <p>
          The fix is one line: move the bundle to the <em>end</em> of
          the chain. unicode-range still gates download, chain order
          determines preference. Native CJK fonts win on every real
          platform; only the iOS Simulator (its actual use case) falls
          through to the bundle.
        </p>
        <p class="thread-note">
          Full diagnosis →
          <a href="/blog/v3-5-5-font-fix-self-hosted-analytics/">v3.5.5 blog post</a>.
          Issue thread →
          <a href="https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/issues/43">#43</a>.
          Reported by <a href="https://github.com/sparkdonn-netizen">@sparkdonn-netizen</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>📊 Self-hosted analytics — Aptabase → Cloudflare D1</h2>
        <p>
          We had been using Aptabase to count app launches and feature
          usage. The dashboard showed ~2 active users despite 3,400+
          downloads, which made it hard to reason about anything. Rather
          than diagnose the third-party SaaS, the entire integration is
          gone — replaced by a single Cloudflare Pages Function backed
          by D1.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Desktop POSTs to <code>solomd.app/api/track</code>. Anonymous device UUID in localStorage. <strong>No IP, no User-Agent, no fingerprint.</strong></li>
          <li>Validator drops anything PII-shaped; returns 204 in every case.</li>
          <li>D1 free tier covers us by 3× at current volume (5M reads/day, 100k writes/day).</li>
          <li>Token-protected dashboard at <code>solomd.app/admin/</code> shows daily activity, version distribution, OS, locale.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Opt-out toggle stays in Settings → 发送匿名使用数据
          (default on). Architecture writeup at <code>web/ANALYTICS.md</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🐛 PR #48 — @beihai23 polish, four small wins</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>PDF export 30-second timeout</strong> — wraps the work in <code>Promise.race</code>; html2pdf.js / Mermaid getting stuck no longer freezes the UI. DOM cleanup is now idempotent.</li>
          <li><strong>Outline button moved into the tab bar</strong> — gone is the floating ≌ at the top-left of the editor. Each Markdown tab now has its own ≌ to toggle the outline pane for that tab.</li>
          <li><strong>Mermaid SVG overlay contrast</strong> — lightbox SVG gets a theme-matching background card (white on light, dark slate on dark).</li>
          <li><strong>HTML cleanup</strong> — wraps <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> rows in <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code>, eliminating a Vite warning.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>🔮 What's next — v3.6</h2>
        <p>
          Issue <a href="https://github.com/zhitongblog/solomd/issues/44">#44</a>
          — image and table inline rendering inside live edit mode — is
          next up. It's a CodeMirror block-decoration extension that
          renders images and tables in their final form when the cursor
          isn't on the source line, and expands to source when the caret
          enters. Not a CSS change; a real editor extension. Beyond #44:
          iPad / Mac App Store resubmission gates queued.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="thanks-row">
        Thanks <strong>@beihai23 (王志刚)</strong> for PR #48 — third
        contribution from this developer, all of them quality fixes —
        and <strong>@sparkdonn-netizen</strong> for the screenshots that
        made #43 actually solvable. Earlier:
        <a href="/blog/">browse the blog →</a>
      </p>
    </article>
    <Giscus lang={lang} />
  </main>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .whats-new { max-width: 820px; padding: 40px 20px 80px; }
  .breadcrumbs { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .breadcrumbs a { color: inherit; }
  .version-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .version-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #000;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .whats-new time { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .whats-new h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); line-height: 1.1; margin: 0 0 22px; }
  .whats-new h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.9rem); margin: 56px 0 16px; }
  .whats-new .lead { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .whats-new p { line-height: 1.75; margin: 12px 0; }
  .whats-new ul, .whats-new ol { padding-left: 22px; }
  .whats-new li { margin: 6px 0; line-height: 1.7; }
  .whats-new code {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.92em;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  /* Inline links are accent-colored; the :not(.btn) excludes CTA
     buttons so the global .btn--primary / .btn--secondary color rules
     win. (Astro scopes this selector with a [data-astro-cid-…] suffix
     which raises specificity above the bare global a.btn--primary,
     hence the explicit exclusion instead of relying on cascade.) */
  .whats-new a:not(.btn) { color: var(--accent); }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 28px 0 8px;
  }
  .thread-note {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
    padding-left: 14px;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }
  .thanks-row {
    margin-top: 64px;
    padding-top: 22px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
